      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HANDS ON TINA (1) slowly into stride off the rails but wound up strongly to score a nose win (22.57) at this track in Grade 5. Good beginner assisted by the inside draw. Expected to measure up again. SAVINA (2) hit the ground running off the tricky draw and gave a sight in front, boxing on well for a minor when third (23.18) at The Gardens in a Grade 5 over 400m. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Leading player again. BIGBAD EDEN (7) was unfavoured last start but gave a huge sight when led for much of the way to place (22.57) at this track in a Grade 5 over 388m. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Leading player again. STAR ZIPPER (8) did the right thing for favourite backers last time and another big run is on the cards.",
